358
00:24:50,200 --> 00:24:51,800
He has reserved it.

359
00:24:51,800 --> 00:24:53,000
It's been reserved?

360
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:54,000
That's right.

361
00:24:54,000 --> 00:24:56,500
A lady just tried the matching wedding dress.

362
00:24:56,500 --> 00:24:58,900
Why don't you try another one?

363
00:24:59,400 --> 00:25:02,200
I want this set. The price is negotiable.

364
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:03,500
What a coincidence.

365
00:25:03,500 --> 00:25:07,600
That lady said the same thing and offered to buy this suit.

366
00:25:07,600 --> 00:25:10,700
Why don't you talk to her about it?

367
00:25:10,700 --> 00:25:13,000
Where is she now?

368
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:14,400
Over there.

369
00:25:14,400 --> 00:25:17,600
Okay. Wait here. I'll take care of it.

370
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:29,800
- Why are you here?
- Why are you here?

371
00:25:29,800 --> 00:25:31,600
- You reserved the wedding dress?
- You reserved the suit?

372
00:25:31,600 --> 00:25:33,300
- I did.
- I did.

373
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:37,900
Why do you want to reserve the suit all of a sudden?

374
00:25:37,900 --> 00:25:38,840
And you?

375
00:25:38,840 --> 00:25:42,070
Why do you want to reserve the wedding dress all of a sudden?

376
00:25:42,070 --> 00:25:43,400
I... None of your business.

377
00:25:43,400 --> 00:25:45,700
Is it because you want to...

378
00:25:48,168 --> 00:25:50,477
Since it's you, I won't take the wedding dress then.

379
00:25:50,477 --> 00:25:52,600
I'll just take the suit.

380
00:25:53,200 --> 00:25:56,400
Are you thinking about...

381
00:26:15,100 --> 00:26:16,400
What's the matter?

382
00:26:16,400 --> 00:26:19,200
Guess who bought the wedding dress?

383
00:26:19,200 --> 00:26:20,400
Cheng Qingcong?

384
00:26:20,400 --> 00:26:21,300
How did you know?

385
00:26:21,300 --> 00:26:23,500
Look at the big smile on your face.

386
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:28,700
Yes!

387
00:26:30,500 --> 00:26:32,600
Look. She's going to propose to me.

388
00:26:32,600 --> 00:26:34,400
She's proposing!

389
00:26:34,400 --> 00:26:37,800
Look. I'm not ready at all.

390
00:26:41,200 --> 00:26:43,700
I don't think it suits you. Take it off.

391
00:26:43,700 --> 00:26:46,000
Take it off! Hurry!

392
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:47,000
Let me try it on.

393
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:48,800
Let me try it, okay?

394
00:27:03,800 --> 00:27:09,000
Are you saying that he wants to propose to me?

395
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:11,000
Didn't you figure it out yourself?

396
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:12,800
Why are you being so shy?

397
00:27:12,800 --> 00:27:14,100
Think about it.

398
00:27:14,100 --> 00:27:16,200
He secretly came here alone to try the suit

399
00:27:16,200 --> 00:27:18,700
and even reserved the matching wedding dress.

400
00:27:18,700 --> 00:27:20,800
What's this if he isn't preparing for a wedding?

401
00:27:20,800 --> 00:27:23,800
But I haven't made up my mind if I want to marry him.

402
00:27:23,800 --> 00:27:25,200
We haven't been together for that long.

403
00:27:25,200 --> 00:27:29,000
My dream of becoming a professional manager has just begun.

404
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:30,500
Enough of the PDA.

405
00:27:30,500 --> 00:27:31,700
Take it.

406
00:27:32,500 --> 00:27:34,800
Since Yan Yuan wants it, I'll let him have it.

407
00:27:34,800 --> 00:27:37,400
I'll only do you the favor this time.

408
00:27:39,200 --> 00:27:41,400
The gentleman next door has tried it on.

409
00:27:41,400 --> 00:27:43,000
Okay.

410
00:27:44,500 --> 00:27:45,600
Look.

411
00:27:45,600 --> 00:27:48,000
He must think you reserved this wedding dress.

412
00:27:48,000 --> 00:27:50,300
That's why he took the matching suit.

413
00:27:51,600 --> 00:27:52,600
You can take it.

414
00:27:52,600 --> 00:27:54,600
Consider it a gift from me.

415
00:27:54,600 --> 00:27:57,100
As for my wedding dress, I'll figure out another way.

416
00:27:57,100 --> 00:28:00,400
I'll need your help to set up the wedding venue.

417
00:28:00,400 --> 00:28:01,600
Don't worry.

418
00:28:01,600 --> 00:28:03,900
Leave it to me.

419
00:28:05,700 --> 00:28:07,800
Such a good girl.

420
00:28:11,200 --> 00:28:12,400
Look.

421
00:28:12,400 --> 00:28:14,000
Take a look!

422
00:28:14,000 --> 00:28:15,700
Take a look!

423
00:28:23,600 --> 00:28:25,800
I look better in it, right?

424
00:28:25,800 --> 00:28:27,500
Take a look.

425
00:28:39,400 --> 00:28:41,500
Miss Song. Miss Song!

426
00:28:41,500 --> 00:28:43,200
Here's your parcel.

427
00:28:43,200 --> 00:28:44,400
Okay. Thank you.

428
00:28:44,400 --> 00:28:45,900
You're welcome.

429
00:28:51,300 --> 00:28:53,800
[Sender, Tang Nuan]

430
00:29:19,968 --> 00:29:22,338
[Tang Nuan]

431
00:29:26,800 --> 00:29:29,500
I've received the USB flash drive. Thank you.

432
00:29:29,500 --> 00:29:31,000
Don't thank me.

433
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:33,300
I didn't take it for you.

434
00:29:33,300 --> 00:29:36,200
I only took it to negotiate with Chen Han.

435
00:29:36,200 --> 00:29:39,000
I have with me here a newly released video.

436
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:41,000
It was never announced before this.

437
00:29:43,800 --> 00:29:45,100
[News Today]
After seeing this video,

438
00:29:45,100 --> 00:29:47,300
you'll believe what I say.

439
00:29:49,400 --> 00:29:50,900
Reporter Tang.

440
00:29:51,900 --> 00:29:53,200
You can really think on your feet.

441
00:29:53,200 --> 00:29:55,200
I admire that.

442
00:29:55,200 --> 00:29:58,000
I thought it was because I didn't explain the script clearly.

443
00:29:58,000 --> 00:30:00,800
It turns out you brought up a new topic during the latter part of the broadcast

444
00:30:00,900 --> 00:30:04,000
and didn't follow the script just to test me.

445
00:30:05,100 --> 00:30:09,200
No matter what the reason is, you've indeed helped us a lot.

446
00:30:09,200 --> 00:30:13,200
The reason I'm calling is to say goodbye to you.

447
00:30:13,200 --> 00:30:15,300
Are you leaving Jiangli?

448
00:30:16,500 --> 00:30:18,200
I've resigned.

449
00:30:18,700 --> 00:30:21,200
I've lost my way for a long time

450
00:30:21,200 --> 00:30:24,800
that I forgot the very reason

451
00:30:24,800 --> 00:30:26,800
that I chose to be in this line.

452
00:30:27,600 --> 00:30:29,500
Well, remember

453
00:30:29,500 --> 00:30:31,600
to carry on my dream as you strive forward.

454
00:30:31,600 --> 00:30:33,200
Okay.

455
00:30:35,300 --> 00:30:37,100
- Do you...
- Actually, I...

456
00:30:38,100 --> 00:30:40,400
Let me go first.

457
00:30:40,400 --> 00:30:42,700
I haven't told you this.

458
00:30:42,700 --> 00:30:45,100
At times,

459
00:30:45,100 --> 00:30:47,000
I really do hate you

460
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:49,000
and get envious of you.

461
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:52,400
But I've never regretted being friends with you.

462
00:30:52,400 --> 00:30:54,800
You might not believe it.

463
00:30:54,800 --> 00:30:57,000
Almost all my laughter and tears

464
00:30:57,000 --> 00:30:59,200
were shared with you.

465
00:31:01,100 --> 00:31:02,800
I never regretted it either.

466
00:31:03,500 --> 00:31:04,600
Oh, right.

467
00:31:04,600 --> 00:31:06,800
I haven't congratulated you and Director Su.

468
00:31:06,800 --> 00:31:08,600
You have to be happy.

469
00:31:09,500 --> 00:31:11,100
Bye, Qingchun.

470
00:31:11,100 --> 00:31:12,400
Bye.

471
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:27,900
It doesn't matter who gets married first.

472
00:31:27,900 --> 00:31:30,200
We have to be each other's bridesmaids.

473
00:31:30,200 --> 00:31:32,000
It's a deal then.

474
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:34,600
One day, when we grow old, we'll quit our job

475
00:31:34,600 --> 00:31:36,400
and travel around the world together.

476
00:31:36,400 --> 00:31:39,300
If so, we'll surely be the youngest

477
00:31:39,300 --> 00:31:41,800
and most fashionable old ladies.

478
00:32:32,130 --> 00:32:39,440
[Travel around the world, starting from here.]

479
00:32:39,440 --> 00:32:40,530
[Travel around the world, starting from here.]

